The set difference between two sets S and T is denoted as S \setminus T. It consists of elements in S that are not in T, defined as: 

1. x \in S \setminus T \iff x \in S \land x \notin T
2. S \setminus T = \{ x \in S : x \notin T \}
3. S \setminus T = \{ x : x \in S \land x \notin T \}

