1591:
Let a, b, c ∈ Z. Then: 
1. lcm{a, gcd{b, c}} = gcd{lcm{a, b}, lcm{a, c}} 
2. gcd{a, lcm{b, c}} = lcm{gcd{a, b}, gcd{a, c}} 

LCM and GCD are distributive over each other.

