Let $x \\in \\mathbb{R}$ be a real number. Let $\lfloor x \rfloor$ denote the floor of $x$, and $\lceil x \rceil$ denote the ceiling of $x$. Then: 
\[ 
\lfloor x \rfloor = \begin{cases} 
\lceil x \rceil & : x \in \mathbb{Z} \\ 
\lceil x \rceil - 1 & : x \notin \mathbb{Z} 
\end{cases} 
\] 
Or equivalently: 
\[ 
\lceil x \rceil = \begin{cases} 
\lfloor x \rfloor & : x \in \mathbb{Z} \\ 
\lfloor x \rfloor + 1 & : x \notin \mathbb{Z} 
\end{cases} 
\] 
Where $\mathbb{Z}$ is the set of integers.

