9960:
Let T be a topological space. Let I = [0, 1] be the closed unit interval. Let a, b, c be distinct points in T. Let f, g: I -> T be arcs from a to b and from b to c, respectively. Define h: I -> T by:

h(x) = { f(2x) for x in [0, 1/2]; g(2x - 1) for x in [1/2, 1]. }

Then either h is an arc in T, or there exists a restriction of h that is an arc in T.
